events.name: GDG Cloud KL Study Session v0.0.1beta
events.description:
BYOC - Bring Your Own Challenge

Details:
This is a focused, comprehensive design challenge/hackathon to review and put into practice contents covered in the Google Professional Cloud Architect exam (https://cloud.google.com/certification/guides/cloud-architect).

It is also an avenue for test takers and professionals to discuss and share ideas related to cloud technology and Google Cloud services, to supplement the regular content in our monthly meetups.

Agenda:
- 6.30 - 7:00 > networking, grab a coffee, get settled.
- 7:00 - 7:30 > Quick introduction, demographic overview, group assignments, problem reveal and definition
- 7.30 - 8.30 > Study/hack/look busy
- 8.30 - 9.00 > Presentation of solution diagrams, peer reviews and
- 9.00 - 9.30 > Questions and Answers, and follow up Questions.

Expectations / !Homework!:

The meetup assumes participants have on them the basics of cloud computing, and additionally familiarity with both popular cloud service vendors and open source solutions.

Challenge yourself to know where you stand with the Practice Exam: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdDAVzEp7b9NvpZYpkkcRATLlRds2q0YYbBYCJ6RRrxMkJvUQ/viewform
- no passing grades, just helps with understanding our first class. More data == Better decisions.

You may also activate your Google cloud account for a head start, but we may not deploy the solutions within the hack session itself.

Other materials:
Getting Started: https://www.coursera.org/specializations/gcp-architecture

events.name: Google Next Extended Mini & Buka Puasa
events.description:
============= LIMITED SEATS ONLY ==================
Get ticket here: https://next-extended-mini.peatix.com

Hey folks!

After Cloud Next Extended in April, we are hosting Mete Atamel from Google for our next event!
Mete is a Senior Developer Advocate at Google, focused on helping developers with Google Cloud. Prior to Google, he worked at Microsoft, Skype, Adobe, EMC, and Nokia building apps and services on various web, mobile and cloud platforms. Originally from the island of Cyprus, he currently lives in Greenwich of London.

And because it's Ramadan, Google Cloud Developer Community Kuala Lumpur will be sponsoring Iftar for us!

Speakers of the evening

Mete Atamel
Title: Serverless with Knative

Talk: When you build a serverless app, you either tie yourself to a cloud provider, or you end up building your own serverless stack. Knative provides a better choice. Knative extends Kubernetes to provide a set of middleware components (build, serving, events) for modern, source-centric, and container-based apps that can run anywhere. In this talk, we’ll see how we can use Knative primitives to build a serverless app that utilizes the Machine Learning magic of the cloud.

Ng Tong Sheng & Faz
Title: Code, Build, Run, and Observe with Google Cloud
Talk: Google Cloud is enabling developers to focus on their code by providing better tools and infrastructure for their backend services. See how Google Cloud make it easy to code, build, run, and observe your applications and services with Google Cloud with an emphasis on Serverless. Demo included!

events.name: Tensorflow x Google Cloud January Meetup

venue.name: ASEAN Data Analytics eXchange (ADAX)
venue.address_1: Vertical Business Suites, Avenue 3, Bangsar South

events.description:
Let's kickstart our very first meetup of the year 2020 in collaboration with the TensorFlow and Deep Learning Malaysia community!

RSVP at http://bit.ly/gdgc-tf-jan

This round we have two Googlers joining us - Valliappa Lakshmanan (Lak) and Felipe Hoffa!

Date: 7th January 2020 (Tuessday)
Time: 6.30 p.m. - 9.00 p.m.
Venue: ASEAN Data Analytics Exchange (ADAX), Level 27, Tower B, Vertical Business Suites Avenue 3, Bangsar South, 59200, Kuala Lumpur.
Map: https://goo.gl/maps/xYzPk4jcrvJHbvWL6

Agenda:
6:30pm Come and Chill + Light Food
7:00pm Start!
7:05pm "Feature Engineering in BigQuery and TensorFlow 2.0/Keras" by Global Head for Data Analytics and AI Solutions on Google Cloud @ Google
8:10pm Short Break
8:30pm Talk 2 by Felipe Hoffa, Developer Advocate for BigQuery @ Google
8:50pm Chill and Network
9:00pm Bye and see you around

Talk 1: "Feature Engineering in BigQuery and TensorFlow 2.0/Keras" by Global Head for Data Analytics and AI Solutions on Google Cloud @ Google

Even today, the most common machine learning problems are predictions using structured data. This talk highlights the importance of feature engineering for structured data predictions, and the challenge that this imposes in terms of training-serving skew. Basic ML concepts are described in SQL syntax of BigQuery. The talk then delves into detail how to carry out such transformations and feature engineering repeatably in Keras and TensorFlow 2.0.

Lak is Global Head for Data Analytics and AI Solutions on Google Cloud. His team builds software solutions for business problems using Google Cloud's data analytics and machine learning products. He founded Google's Advanced Solutions Lab ML Immersion program and is the author of a couple of O'Reilly books and several Coursera courses. Before Google, Lak was a Director of Data Science at Climate Corporation and a Research Scientist at NOAA.

​Follow him on Twitter at @lak_gcp, read articles by him on Medium, and see more details at www.vlakshman.com

Talk 2: Topic to be confirmed, by Felipe Hoffa, Developer Advocate for BigQuery @ Google

See you in the Cloud! RSVP at http://bit.ly/gdgc-tf-jan
